11/11/2010
VATICAN CITY/PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Montenegrin Parliament Speaker Ranko Krivokapic invited Pope Benedict XVI to visit Montenegro as soon as possible, his cabinet announced after a meeting between the two in the Vatican on Wednesday (November 10th). 
The Pope thanked for the invitation and praised Montenegro's policy of multi-religious and multiethnic tolerance. 
(RTCG, Radio Free Europe - 10/11/10)
